      "writtenOn": "2019-07-17T15:54:35Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Dawn uses SPIR-V exclusively as its shading language, and translates it internally to the platform-specific ones where required (MSL, HLSL, GLSL). Passing the native shading language through would be difficult, since new API entry points would have to be added as an extension to Dawn, and as you say, the bindings might be tricky as well. It\u0027s also kind of contrary to the spirit of the API.\n\nThe only thing I had to add (back) to SkSL was the separate sampler and texture datatypes, since Dawn doesn\u0027t support combined samplers and textures. For the most part, everything else just works.",
